# Clean Code Rules

## Forbidden Patterns

```ts
// ❌ Raw fetch in client components
const res = await fetch("/api/leads");

// ✅ Always apiAxios
const res = await apiAxios.get(API.LEADS.LIST);
```

```ts
// ❌ Legacy import
import { useListLeads } from "@/src/lib/api-client-react";

// ✅ Module service hook
import { useLeads } from "@/src/modules/admin/leads";
```

```ts
// ❌ Hardcoded route
router.push("/admin/leads");

// ✅ Route constant
router.push(ROUTES.ADMIN.LEADS);
```

```ts
// ❌ Legacy toast
const { toast } = useToast();
toast({ title: "Saved" });

// ✅ Sonner
import { toast } from "sonner";
toast.success("Saved");
toast.error("Failed to save.");
```

## Backend Service Rules

```ts
// ❌ Logic in route handler
router.post("/leads", async (req, res) => {
  const lead = await db.insert(leadsTable).values(req.body); // Never
});

// ✅ Service call only in routes
router.post(ROUTE_PATHS.LEADS.LIST, async (req, res) => {
  const parsed = CreateLeadBody.safeParse(req.body);
  if (!parsed.success) { res.status(400).json({ error: "Invalid body" }); return; }
  const lead = await createLead(parsed.data);
  res.status(201).json(lead);
});
```

## Audit Logging (Backend — Required on All Mutations)

```ts
// In service layer — every create/update/delete must log
logAction("create", "CRM", `New inquiry from ${data.fullName}`, { leadId: lead.id }).catch(() => {});
logAction("update", "Projects", `Project #${id} updated`, { id }).catch(() => {});
logAction("delete", "Documents", `Document #${id} deleted`, { id }).catch(() => {});
```

## No Dead Code

- Remove unused imports immediately
- Never leave TODO comments without a linked task
- Never leave `console.log` in production code — use `logger.info()` (backend)
